#pixel size and data normalisation

new_df['Lipid Volume']=(new_df['Pixel size']**3)*(new_df['Lipid Volume'])
new_df['Lipid Volume']=(new_df['Lipid Volume']-new_df['Lipid Volume'].min())/(new_df['Lipid Volume'].max()-new_df['Lipid Volume'].min())

In [14]:
# Plot histograms of normalized lipid volumes by LAC for each state
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8), dpi=600)
sns.set_style("white")
sns.set_style("whitegrid")

states = new_df['State'].unique()

for state in states:
    state_data = new_df[new_df['State'] == state]
    plt.hist(state_data['Lipid LAC'], 
             bins=20, 
             weights=state_data['Lipid Volume'], 
             label=state, 
             alpha=0.5, 
             edgecolor='black', 
             color=state_colors[state]) 

plt.xlabel('Lipid droplet LAC, $\mu$m$^{-1}$', fontsize=18)
plt.ylabel('Lipid droplet normalized volume', fontsize=18)
plt.tick_params(axis='x', labelsize=15)
plt.tick_params(axis='y', labelsize=15)
plt.legend().remove()

plt.savefig('F:\\Microglia project\\Soft X-ray tomography\\2023\Analysis\\Graphs\\LD_LAC_V_mass.png',dpi=600, bbox_inches='tight')

# Plot histograms of normalized lipid volumes by LAC for lipid droplet class estimation
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8), dpi=600)
sns.set_style("white")
sns.set_style("whitegrid")

states = new_df['State'].unique()


for state in states:
    state_data = new_df[new_df['State'] == state]
    plt.hist(state_data['Lipid LAC'], 
             bins=20, 
             weights=state_data['Lipid Volume'], 
             label=state, 
             alpha=0.5, 
             edgecolor='black', 
             color='gray') 

plt.xlabel('Lipid droplet LAC, $\mu$m$^{-1}$', fontsize=18)
plt.ylabel('Lipid droplet normalized volume', fontsize=18)
plt.tick_params(axis='x', labelsize=15)
plt.tick_params(axis='y', labelsize=15)
plt.legend().remove()
